/**
 * default-data.js
 * Built-in example dataset and pre-filled model strings for FANGS.
 *
 * The CSV matches data/example.csv, generated by tests/r-reference/generate-default-data.R
 * with set.seed(42):
 *   y_i = 2 + 1.5*x_i + b_{group[i]} + eps_i       (continuous response)
 *   b_group ~ N(0, sigma_b^2), sigma_b = 0.5
 *   eps_i   ~ N(0, sigma^2),   sigma   = 0.7
 * N=50, 5 groups (10 obs each).
 *
 * Additional columns derived from x (GLM examples, independent of y):
 *   y_count ~ Poisson(exp(1.0 + 0.5 * x))  — for Poisson GLM
 *   y_bin   ~ Bernoulli(plogis(1.5 * x))   — for Bernoulli GLM
 *
 * OLS sanity check: alpha ≈ 2.29, beta ≈ 1.38 (close to true values after
 * accounting for absorbed group effects in the simple linear model).
 *
 * Note: FANGS uses SD parameterisation for dnorm. Priors on regression
 * coefficients use dnorm(mean, sigma) where sigma is the SD (here SD=5,
 * giving a weakly informative prior). Variance components use dunif(0, 100).
 */

